employee expense line API

Employee expense lines

Details for each expense line on the employee expense report.

Get an employee expense line

Returns a collection with a key, ID, and link for each employee expense line.

Responses

http://localhost:3000/objects/employee-expense-line

  • 400

Create an employee expense line

Creates a new employee expense line.

Request Body schema: application/json
entryDate
string <date>

Expense line date.

txnCurrency
string

Expense line currency.

txnAmount
required
string <decimal-precision-2>

Expense line amount.

quantity
string <decimal-precision-2>

Quantity for a rate-based expense.(example- mileage)

unitRate
string <decimal-precision-2>

Unit rate for a rate-based expense (example- mileage)

paidTo
string

Paid to.

paidFor
string

Paid for.

object (account)
object (expenseType)
object (Reimbursement currency to Base currency conversion data)
object (currency)
isBillable
boolean
Default: false

Expense line that is billable.Use false for No, true for Yes.

object (form1099)
object (reimbursementInformation)
object (dimensions)
object (employeeExpense)

http://localhost:3000/objects/employee-expense-line

Create a project

Creates a new project.

id is required if document sequencing is not enabled for projects in the company. If document sequencing is enabled, you can provide an id value to use instead of the document sequence value.

Request Body schema: application/json

project definition

id
required
string

Unique identifier for the project.

name
string

Project name.

description
string

A brief description of the project.

projectCurrency
string

Currency used for project budget information.

category
string
Enum: "contract" "capitalized" "internalNonBillable" "internalBillable"

Project category. Used for filtering and reporting.

object

Project status

startDate
string <date>

Date on which the project is scheduled to begin.

endDate
string <date>

Date on which the project is scheduled to end.

object
contractAmount
string <decimal-precision-2>

The contracted amount for the project for reporting purposes.

object

Project progress

billingType
string
Enum: "timeAndMaterial" "fixedFee" "fixedFeeAndExpenses"

Billing type specifies how the project will be invoiced.

salesOrderNumber
string

Sales order number for the project, for reference.

purchaseOrderNumber
string

Purchase order number for the project, for reference.

purchaseOrderAmount
string <decimal-precision-2>

Project purchase order amount, for reference.

purchaseQuoteNumber
string

Project purchase quote number, for reference.

documentNumber
string

An external reference number that can be used to report on the project in custom reports.

object

The parent project if this project is the child of another, larger project.

invoiceWithParent
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to include the project's transactions in invoices for the parent project.

object

The customer associated with the project.

object

The sales contact for the project.

object

Project type, used to categorize and report on projects.

object

Project manager employee for the project. Project managers usually approve timesheets and expense reports. Project managers can also run and view project reports.

object

The department associated with this project. The project department overrides any department associated with an employee on a timesheet. If a project department is not set, the employee department is used.

object

The location associated with this project. The project location overrides any location associated with an employee on a timesheet. If a project location is not set, the employee location is used.

object

The Accounts Receivable payment terms for the project. The payment terms are included on the invoice header. If project payment terms are not set, the customer's terms are used.

object

A Sage Intacct user assigned as a customer representative with the ability to approve timesheets for the project.

object

Class dimension used to track the project.

userRestrictions
string
Default: "systemDefault"
Enum: "systemDefault" "anyUser" "projectUsers" "projectTaskUsers"

User restrictions for entering project time and expenses (overrides default user restrictions for the Projects application).

isBillableEmployeeExpense
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill employee expenses for the project.

isBillablePurchasingAPExpense
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill project purchases entered through Accounts Payable or Purchasing.

object

Rates and Pricing

object

invoiceCurrency
string

string
Default: "doNothing"
Enum: "doNothing" "issueAWarningMessage" "preventBilling"

Billing control to prevent or warn of billings that exceed the project's budgeted billing amount.

excludeExpenses
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to exclude employee, Accounts Payable (AP), and purchase order expenses from the over-budget calculation

object

The contract that this project is associated with.

object

Documents associated with the project, such as statements of work, specifications, or agreements.

object

The top-level project that this project descends from.

object

Grant-related fields.

path Parameters
key
required
string

System-assigned key for the project.

Request Body schema: application/json
name
string

Project name.

description
string

A brief description of the project.

projectCurrency
string

Currency used for project budget information.

category
string
Enum: "contract" "capitalized" "internalNonBillable" "internalBillable"

Project category. Used for filtering and reporting.

object

Project status

startDate
string <date>

Date on which the project is scheduled to begin.

endDate
string <date>

Date on which the project is scheduled to end.

object
contractAmount
string <decimal-precision-2>

The contracted amount for the project for reporting purposes.

object

Project progress

billingType
string
Enum: "timeAndMaterial" "fixedFee" "fixedFeeAndExpenses"

Billing type specifies how the project will be invoiced.

salesOrderNumber
string

Sales order number for the project, for reference.

purchaseOrderNumber
string

Purchase order number for the project, for reference.

purchaseOrderAmount
string <decimal-precision-2>

Project purchase order amount, for reference.

purchaseQuoteNumber
string

Project purchase quote number, for reference.

documentNumber
string

An external reference number that can be used to report on the project in custom reports.

object

The parent project if this project is the child of another, larger project.

invoiceWithParent
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to include the project's transactions in invoices for the parent project.

object

The customer associated with the project.

object

The sales contact for the project.

object

Project type, used to categorize and report on projects.

object

Project manager employee for the project. Project managers usually approve timesheets and expense reports. Project managers can also run and view project reports.

object

The department associated with this project. The project department overrides any department associated with an employee on a timesheet. If a project department is not set, the employee department is used.

object

The location associated with this project. The project location overrides any location associated with an employee on a timesheet. If a project location is not set, the employee location is used.

object

The Accounts Receivable payment terms for the project. The payment terms are included on the invoice header. If project payment terms are not set, the customer's terms are used.

object

A Sage Intacct user assigned as a customer representative with the ability to approve timesheets for the project.

object

Class dimension used to track the project.

userRestrictions
string
Default: "systemDefault"
Enum: "systemDefault" "anyUser" "projectUsers" "projectTaskUsers"

User restrictions for entering project time and expenses (overrides default user restrictions for the Projects application).

isBillableEmployeeExpense
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill employee expenses for the project.

isBillablePurchasingAPExpense
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill project purchases entered through Accounts Payable or Purchasing.

object

Rates and Pricing

object

Contacts associated with the project.

invoiceMessage
string

Message to appear on invoices.

invoiceCurrency
string

Currency to use when generating invoices for the project.

billingOverMax
string
Default: "doNothing"
Enum: "doNothing" "issueAWarningMessage" "preventBilling"

Billing control to prevent or warn of billings that exceed the project's budgeted billing amount.

excludeExpenses
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to exclude employee, Accounts Payable (AP), and purchase order expenses from the over-budget calculation

object

The contract that this project is associated with.

object

Documents associated with the project, such as statements of work, specifications, or agreements.

object

The top-level project that this project descends from.

object

Grant-related fields.

status
string (status)
Default: "active"
Enum: "active" "inactive"

Object status.

Tasks

A unit of work to be performed for a project. Use tasks to:

  • Track project work by task and assigned resources.
  • Identify which tasks are billable to the customer.
  • Enter estimated and planned hours, track percent completed as the task progresses, and create recurring schedules.
  • Create task dependencies so one task doesn't start until another finishes.
  • Set other optional information, such as the priority or status of the task.

List tasks

Returns up to 100 object references from the collection with a key, ID, and link for each task. This operation is mostly for use in testing; use query to find tasks that meet certain criteria and to specify properties that are returned.

Responses

http://localhost:3000/objects/task

  • 400

Create a task

Creates a new project task.

Request Body schema: application/json

New task definition

id
required
string

Identifier for the task. Must be unique within the project. 20 characters max.

name
string

Task name. Must be unique within the project.

object

The parent task if this task is the child of another, larger task.

object

The project that the task is associated with.

object

The customer that this task will be billed to.

object

Work item that this task is assigned to. A task must be assigned to an item for it to be invoiced.

object

Planned start and end dates for the task.

object

Actual task start and end dates.

object

Task-related durations.

description
string

Task description.

isMilestone
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to indicate that the task is a milestone.

isUtilized
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to mark this task as utilized. A utilized task is one spent making progress on a customer project or internal project. A non-utilized task is one spent not working on a customer project or internal project, for example, time spent filling in an expense report or timesheet.

isBillable
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill the work for the task. Set to false to mark the task as non-billable.

wbsCode
string

Work breakdown structure code.

priority
number

A numeric value indicating the task priority.

status
string
Default: "inProgress"
Enum: "notStarted" "planned" "inProgress" "completed" "onHold"

Current status of the task. If the task status is Completed, employees can't enter time for the task on timesheets.

object

Time type used when posting labor costs to the general ledger or for tracking and reporting how work time is spent.

object

Class dimension associated with the task.

object

Documents associated with the task, such as statements of work, specifications, or agreements.

object

Task that must be completed before this task can start.

object

Production Units

object

The top-level task that this task descends from.

object

The standard task that is the template for this task.

Set to true to mark this task as utilized. A utilized task is one spent making progress on a customer project or internal project. A non-utilized task is one spent not working on a customer project or internal project, for example, time spent filling in an expense report or timesheet.

isBillable
boolean
Default: false

Set to true to bill the work for the task. Set to false to mark the task as non-billable.

wbsCode
string

Work breakdown structure code.

priority
number

A numeric value indicating the task priority.

status
string
Default: "inProgress"
Enum: "notStarted" "planned" "inProgress" "completed" "onHold"

Current status of the task. If the task status is Completed, employees can't enter time for the task on timesheets.

object

Time type used when posting labor costs to the general ledger or for tracking and reporting how work time is spent.

object

Class dimension associated with the task.

object

Documents associated with the task, such as statements of work, specifications, or agreements.

object

Task that must be completed before this task can start.

object

Production Units

object

The top-level task that this task descends from.

object

The standard task that is the template for this task.

Timesheet lines

A timesheet line is an entry on a timesheet that represents work done by one employee on a single day. Each timesheet line should reflect the dimensions used by the company. That is, work done for one customer or project should be recorded in a separate timesheet line from work done for another customer or project, etc. Reports and invoices use the dimension values to group timesheet lines for billing.

List timesheet lines

Returns up to 100 object references from the collection with a key, ID, and link for each timesheet line. This operation is mostly for use in testing; use query to find timesheet lines that meet certain criteria and to specify properties that are returned.

Timesheets

Timesheets ensure workers are paid appropriately and help project managers invoice clients and track overall project costs and expenses over time.

Timesheets are used in both Projects and Time & Expenses. A subscription to Projects is required to approve timesheets and save timesheets as drafts.

Each time a timesheet entry is submitted, a timesheet approval history object is created for tracking purposes.

List timesheets

Returns up to 100 object references from the collection with a key, ID, and link for each timesheet. This operation is mostly for use in testing; use query to find timesheets that meet certain criteria and to specify properties that are returned.

Update a timesheet

Updates an existing timesheet by setting field values. Any fields not provided remain unchanged.

path Parameters
key
required
string

System-assigned unique key for the timesheet.

Request Body schema: application/json
beginDate
string <date>

Begin date of the work period.

postingDate
string <date>

GL posting date.

state
string
Default: "draft"
Enum: "submitted" "approved" "partiallyApproved" "declined" "draft" "partiallyDeclined" "saved"

State.

description
string

Timesheet description.

object

The employee who did the work.

object

Supporting document.

Array of objects (timesheet-line)

Time entries

Responses

http://localhost:3000/objects/timesheet/{key}

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "state": "submitted",
  • "description": "Week of 01/01/23"
}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 400
Content type
application/json
{
  • "ia::result": {
    • "key": "40",
    • "id": "40",
    • "href": "/objects/timesheet/40"
    },
  • "ia::meta": {
    • "totalCount": 1
    }
}
